{# PRD Generation Prompt - A1 Software/SaaS #}
<role>
You are an expert product manager creating an MVP Product Requirements Document (PRD) for a Software/SaaS product.
</role>

<template_info>
Template: A1 - Software / SaaS Product
Examples: CRM for clinics, farmer advisory app, school management system, B2B tools
</template_info>

<context_pack>
Project Metadata:
- Title: {{ summarized_context.metadata.project_title }}
- Description: {{ summarized_context.metadata.project_description }}
- Industry: {{ summarized_context.metadata.industry or "Not specified" }}
- Geography: {{ summarized_context.metadata.geography or "Not specified" }}

{{ summarized_context.vps_v2_summary }}

{{ summarized_context.bmc_v2_summary }}

{{ summarized_context.solution_critique_summary }}

{% if summarized_context.vpc_v2_summary %}
{{ summarized_context.vpc_v2_summary }}
{% endif %}
</context_pack>

<user_clarifying_answers>
{% for qa in clarifying_answers %}
Q{{ qa.q_index }}: {{ clarifying_questions[qa.q_index - 1].question_text }}
A{{ qa.q_index }}: {{ qa.answer_text }}
{% endfor %}
</user_clarifying_answers>

{% if research_results %}
<research_insights>
{% for finding in research_results.findings %}
- {{ finding }}
{% endfor %}
</research_insights>
{% endif %}

<task>
Generate a complete MVP PRD for this Software/SaaS product. Follow the A1 template structure.
</task>

<required_sections>
1. Purpose (Defines the core reason this MVP exists and the validated problem it addresses)
2. Objective (Specifies what we aim to learn and how we measure success)
3. Scope (Clarifies what is included and excluded from this MVP release)
4. Primary Persona (Describes the target user and their primary job to be done)
5. Must-Have Features (Essential features required for MVP launch with FAB analysis)
6. Nice-to-Have Features (Deferred features with rationale for postponement)
7. Critical Workflows (End-to-end user journeys that must work flawlessly)
8. Data Requirements (Defines user inputs and system outputs needed)
9. Automation Level (Specifies manual vs automated processes and AI features)
10. Platform Choices (Determines primary platform and access methods)
11. Constraints (Technical, operational, and scope limitations)
12. Success Signals (Quantitative metrics and qualitative indicators of success)
13. Assumptions & Risks (Key assumptions with risk analysis and mitigations)
</required_sections>

<quantity_requirements>
- Must-have features: Generate 5-7 features (not 3), each linked to a Job from VPC
- Nice-to-have features: Generate 3-5 features deferred to later with clear deferral reasoning
- Critical workflows: Generate 3 essential user journeys with 5-8 detailed steps each
- Success metrics: Generate 3-4 quantitative metrics and 2 qualitative signals
- Assumptions: Generate 4 key assumptions with detailed risk analysis and mitigation
- Constraints: Generate 4-5 constraints across different categories
- Learning goals: Generate 3 specific learning goals
- Out of scope items: Generate 5-6 items that are explicitly excluded
</quantity_requirements>

<depth_requirements>
Feature descriptions (50-100 words each):
- Explain WHAT the feature does in detail
- Explain HOW it works from user perspective
- Include edge cases or important behaviors
- Reference specific user needs it addresses

Workflow steps (15-30 words each step):
- Include specific user actions and system responses
- Mention timing expectations where relevant
- Include error handling or alternative paths
- Make steps actionable and testable

Persona description (100-150 words):
- Include demographic details, daily routine, pain frequency
- Describe current workarounds and frustrations
- Include emotional context and motivations
- Reference specific quotes or behaviors from research

Assumptions (detailed analysis):
- State the assumption clearly
- Explain WHY this assumption matters
- Quantify the risk if wrong
- Provide specific, actionable mitigation steps

Purpose statement (75-100 words):
- Clearly articulate the validated problem with evidence
- Explain why NOW is the right time to build this
- Connect to business opportunity
</depth_requirements>

<enum_values>
Use ONLY these exact values:
- job_type: "functional" | "emotional" | "social"
- primary_platform: "web" | "mobile" | "both" | "desktop" | "sms" | "ussd" | "voice" | "whatsapp" | "telegram" | "api" | "pos" | "kiosk" | "embedded"
- access_method: "login" | "link" | "access_code" | "public" | "sms_shortcode" | "ussd_code" | "phone_call" | "qr_code" | "api_key" | "oauth" | "biometric" | "pin" | "no_auth"
- output_type: "dashboard" | "report" | "alert" | "notification" | "export" | "message" | "sms" | "email" | "document" | "receipt" | "certificate" | "invoice" | "confirmation" | "response" | "file" | "api_response"
- constraint_category: "feature" | "integration" | "technical" | "compliance" | "scope" | "operational" | "resource" | "timeline" | "budget" | "regulatory" | "security" | "scalability" | "geographic"
- confidence: "low" | "medium" | "high"
</enum_values>

